y & Audit Dashboard (/dashboard/audit)Global Operations Log: Table tracking every critical user event (Login attempts, punch edits, shift schedule overrides) displaying Timestamp, User IP, Action Performed, and Device OS metadata.Hardware Telemetry Check: Status board tracking network uptime, firmware versions, and tamper alerts for remote terminal components.📈 Scalability RequirementsDatabase Optimization: Ensure PostgreSQL indexes are generated for employee_id, timestamp, and location_id fields to optimize heavy query sorting over hundreds of thousands of historical punch logs.Asynchronous Processing: Long-running analytics and heavy report compilation (PDF/Excel generation) must happen via asynchronous background queues using Nitro utilities or Redis hooks so as not to block user dashboard requests.State Hydration Efficiency: Use Nuxt 4 useAsyncData with unique keys to avoid duplicate endpoint hydration during server-to-client UI rendering cycles.🛠️ Step-By-Step Implementation StrategyWhen building with me, tackle tasks in this precise order:Phase 1: Foundation Setup — Initialize the Nuxt 4 app structure, setup Tailwind CSS + UI components, establish the Database Schema with Prisma/Drizzle containing optimized index setups.Phase 2: Secure Backend API Architecture — Write the security global middleware layer (Rate limiting, CORS, Security headers) and core validation utilities.Phase 3: The Data Sync Interface — Build the Nitro endpoints meant for receiving real-time input from the biometric scanners securely.Phase 4: Dashboard UI Implementation — Create the operations feed, the high-level executive panel, and the unmodifiable auditor logs.Phase 5: Analytical Reports Generator — Build the automated calculation script for complex aviation rolling shifts and overtime exports.
